<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/241271-historical-president">Historical President?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_241271'><a id="like_count_community_question_241271" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/241271?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">6 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F33512.One_Thousand_White_Women">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/241271-historical-president">7 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/241271-historical-president">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1178619-elizabeth"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1481305415i/1178619._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1178619-elizabeth">Elizabeth</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Ulysses S. Grant was a president, but he wasn&apos;t a drunk like the book portrays him. Andrew Jackson was the Indian killer (Trail of Tears). Actually, G<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Ulysses S. Grant was a president, but he wasn't a drunk like the book portrays him. Andrew Jackson was the Indian killer (Trail of Tears). Actually, Grant suffered from severe migraines, but the troops chalked it up to hangovers. Those closest to Grant said he was a sober man and didn't drink. Grant did try to initiate Peace Policies with tribes, and replaced cruel Indian Agents with Christian Missionaries. Not that it was a major improvement, but he wasn't quite as horrible as the book would have the reader believe.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link224205" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=224205&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F241271-historical-president%2Fanswers%2F224205-ulysses-s-grant-was-a">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

</div>
</div>

</div>

